==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oviparous
<hw>O*vip"a*rous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>oviparus</ets>; <ets>ovum</ets> egg + <ets>parere</ets> to bring
forth: cf. F. <ets>ovipare</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Producing young from eggs; <as>as, an <ex>oviparous</ex> animal, in
which the egg is generally separated from the animal, and hatched after
exclusion</as>; -- opposed to <contr>viviparous</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oviposit</ent>⟦br⟧
